<p>(a)	ADC shall be excused from, and shall not be liable for, any delay in its performance under this Agreement due to causes beyond ADC’s reasonable control and not occasioned by its fault or negligence. Such causes shall include an Act of God (including natural causes, exclusively without human Intervention, which could not have been prevented by any amount of foresight or care), acts of government or government regulations, fire, flood, earthquake, riot, insurrection, terrorism, strike or force majeure, or any other cause beyond the reasonable control of ADC (hereinafter "Force Majeure and other delays which shall include, but not be limited to: delay in the providing customer supplied purchased parts, components, or other materials; failure to perform on the part of ADC’s vendors and subcontractors or Additional Services (if any) requested by Customer which may impact this original General Terms Agreement or work schedule, and any other cause which is beyond the reasonable control of ADC. (hereinafter "Excusable Delay").</p>
<p>(b)	Customer shall use its best effort to avoid causing a delay in commencement of work or any work stoppage by failure to provide the current and complete technical data, authorizations or other requirements needed to redeliver the Equipment and effect payment for the Service(s) rendered. In the event Customer causes a delay in commencement of work or any work stoppage by failure to provide any of the above listed Items, ADC shall have the right to request immediate payment for the balance chargeable for the Work Scope plus payment for all Additional Services already approved by the Customer.</p>
<p>(c)	If any Force Majeure event occurs which affects the performance of obligations under this Agreement, that Party shall make its best efforts to promptly notify the other Party of such an event occurring, followed by confirmation in writing detailing the event and its effect, and an estimate of the length of time for which fulfillment of its obligations will be affected.</p>
<p>(d)	Neither Party shall be deemed to be In breach of this Agreement for any delay In the performance of its obligations herein (excluding the obligation to pay without delay the price of the Service(s) hereunder), to the extent that such delay or non-performance is due to any Force Majeure event, and the time for performance of that obligation shall be extended accordingly.</p>
<p>(e)	Upon cessation of the Force Majeure event, the affected Party shall promptly inform the other Party of such cessation, and as soon as reasonably practicable thereafter, resume the performance of the obligations hereunder.</p>
<p>(f) Neither party shall be liable for any damage or delays caused by force majeure including Acts of God, war, natural disaster, floods, explosions, fires, earthquakes, tornados, failure of transportation, strikes or other labor disputes, or any other cause beyond the reasonable control of ADC.</p>
